 >> Bentley(ch. 8 p.24 sec 8.2)reccomends using a wheel puller. Any good tool rental place should have one.

> I can't see how that puller works even after looking at the picture. It's
> pulling on the studs by pushing on the hub in the center but the studs
> > aren't attached to the drum. Whuh?

 That puller will pull off the hub AND drum as a unit IF the big center nut is removed 1st.
 It will not remove a drum from the hub.
